  "body": "We've had a few questions about what happened to ERC20Mintable in 3.x. See [this thread in the forum](https://forum.openzeppelin.com/t/where-is-erc20mintable-sol-in-openzeppelin-contracts-3-0/2283). I think the answers in the thread are good but we might want to feature this in the docs themselves. Someone suggested to add a note in the API page for ERC20.\r\n\r\nMaybe we're also missing a more general note about how the \"core\" set of contracts is designed to be unopinionated, while the presets implement more opinionated patterns.",
